1
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:10,700
Yang, your good brother Luo Zhengqiang owes us ten thousand yuan.

2
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:13,210
Paying back debts is only right, isn't it?

3
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,690
Luo Zhengqiang.

4
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,880
Luo Zhengqiang, get out here.

5
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,840
You borrowed ten thousand yuan from them, didn't you?

6
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,000
Mr. Sun.

7
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,600
This is all I have right now.

8
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:44,680
Take this for now.

9
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:47,740
Just this much?

10
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,200
I'll make up the rest as soon as possible.

11
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,039
Fine. For Yang Gang's sake today,

12
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:55,970
I'll let you off the hook this time.

13
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,920
Pay off the rest in three months.

14
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,760
I will.

15
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,040
Also, Yang Gang.

16
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,720
Business is business.

17
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,600
Borrowed money follows the rules.

18
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,259
Interest must be paid on time.

19
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,280
Okay.

20
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,680
Just three months.

21
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:14,720
Let's go.

22
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,160
Why did you borrow money?

23
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:27,640
Godmother is in the hospital and needs money for treatment.

24
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,360
I just thought, what if I got a lucky break?

25
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,280
Then I could pay the medical bills, right?

26
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,610
How much did you borrow?

27
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,720
I borrowed...

28
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,480
Five thousand yuan.

29
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,000
I didn't expect the interest to snowball like that.

30
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,200
To over ten thousand.

31
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,120
I've told you so many times, brother.

32
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,320
Don't you understand?

33
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,000
Brother.

34
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,220
I'm telling you, Luo Zhengqiang.

35
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,540
If you touch that stuff again,

36
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,810
I'll send you straight to the cops.

37
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,060
Gang, Qiang did it for our godmother too.

38
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:00,800
Brother.

39
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,850
We have to think of a way now.

40
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:12,400
You gave all the settlement money Xiao Tianman gave you to Sun.

41
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,880
What about Godmother's medical bills?

42
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,560
There must be another way.

43
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,640
Let's think again.

44
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,760
Brother.

45
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,760
I... I really made a mistake.

46
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,400
As things stand,

47
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,480
there's only one way left.

48
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,360
What way?

49
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,360
Stealing ore.

50
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,280
Quiet, everyone.

51
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,530
I want to ask you all a question.

52
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:55,440
How has Manager Xiao treated everyone all these years?

53
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,160
For so many years,

54
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:03,290
has Manager Xiao ever shortchanged us a single cent?

55
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,000
Now comes this Shanshui Group.

56
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,900
Under the banner of mine restructuring,

57
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,850
they want to replace labor with machines.

58
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,160
Do you know what labor is?

59
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,959
It's every single one of you standing here.

60
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:19,680
It means layoffs, unemployment.

61
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,000
No money to earn.

62
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:25,600
And our good brother Yang Gang,

63
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,840
is colluding with Shanshui Group.

64
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,320
He kidnapped Manager Xiao.

65
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,180
To force our mine to restructure.

66
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,520
Do you think we can accept that?

67
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,320
No!

68
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:37,440
We can't let Shanshui Group take away our livelihoods.

69
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,680
Yang Gang is a real scumbag.

70
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,210
Helping Shanshui Group bully our own people.

71
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,560
We misjudged him.

72
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:45,890
Honestly, Yang Gang actually thought they were on his side.

73
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,040
Come on, come in and drink.

74
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:57,170
We were just waiting for you. Hurry up.

75
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,490
Look how much he's had to drink.

76
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:23,960
Gang.

77
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,600
These are all abandoned mine shafts.

78
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,200
They were mined out long ago.

79
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:30,420
Are you soft in the head or something?

80
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,760
Let's go steal ore from an active mine.

81
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,850
That's just turning ourselves in.

82
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,280
Mines are abandoned due to efficiency,

83
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:39,080
not because they're empty.

84
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:39,840
You know?

85
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,560
Look.

86
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,650
Three mountains, four hidden.

87
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,570
Small gullies have mouths.

88
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,060
Big gullies have legs.

89
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,159
Gold comes from the shady slope.

90
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:54,600
Bro, what does that mean?

91
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,020
It's an old miners' rhyme.

92
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,960
The "three mountains, four hidden"...

93
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,600
refers to the top of the pincer-shaped mountains in the valley,

94
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,040
or the river bends.

95
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,370
In front of the mountain facing the river,

96
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,970
that's where gold gathers.

97
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,250
Small gullies have mouths.

98
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:14,520
What does "Big legs have ditches" mean?

99
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,400
Bro is being dirty.

100
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:18,690
It's "Small gullies have mouths".

101
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,600
It refers to the mouth of a small gully.

102
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,640
There's placer gold there.

103
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,000
And "Big gullies have legs"?

104
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,080
It means larger river valleys.

105
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,360
They have placer gold.

106
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,120
Including their upstream tributaries.

107
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,240
Gold comes from the shady slope.

108
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,100
I know that one.

109
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,920
Oh, you know it now?

110
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,280
Gold on the shady slope,

111
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,520
means placer gold

112
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:39,720
usually appears on the shady side of the valley.

113
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,120
Smart, right?

114
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,159
Let's go.

115
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,600
Come on.

116
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,200
This is it.

117
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,980
There should be placer gold here.

118
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,160
Bro.

119
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,410
I know this abandoned mine.

120
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,160
It collapsed before.

121
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,480
People died here.

122
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,520
I heard about that too.

123
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,440
People died here.

124
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,160
And it's haunted.

125
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,330
The three of us are ghosts, too.

126
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:32,720
Poor ghosts.

127
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:38,840
Poor ghosts.

128
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,400
Poor ghosts, lend a hand.

129
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,600
Hurry.

130
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,600
Wait.

131
00:07:53,159 --> 00:07:54,360
Bro, come here quick.

132
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,040
Here, give me some light.

133
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,400
Give me light.

134
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,730
We need to break through this wall.

135
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:33,080
Seems like we'll only find copper here.

136
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,080
If gold were that easy to find,

137
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,809
it wouldn't be worth anything.

138
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:39,000
Copper sells too.

139
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:40,960
Dig.

140
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,240
Come on.

141
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,160
Remember,

142
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:04,040
follow... follow the edge here.

143
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,900
Go slow on the corners.

144
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:15,560
Sis,

145
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,440
have you heard?

146
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,360
Xiao Tianman is hiring an assistant at the mine.

147
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,360
I want to go.

148
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,240
Sounds nice.

149
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,940
But it's not an assistant job.

150
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,480
He's just looking for a mistress.

151
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,520
Don't go.

152
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,400
That's because they have no self-respect.

153
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,960
I can control myself.

154
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,840
I'll quit while I'm ahead.

155
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,480
That is Xiao Tianman.

156
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,000
You think you'll have a choice then?

157
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:41,720
Sis,

158
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,600
I'll tell you the truth.

159
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,640
My parents worked hard to raise me.

160
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:50,000
I can't repay them.

161
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:53,040
Xiao Tianman pays well.

162
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,010
One month earns more than three months of mining.

163
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,640
My mom isn't well.

164
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,920
We'll have a lot of expenses later.

165
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,640
Xiaomei, you're my best friend.

166
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,840
I can't just watch you walk into a trap.

167
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:14,720
If you're in danger,

168
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,380
call the police immediately.

169
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,360
Don't worry.

170
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,170
If it doesn't work out, I'll leave.

171
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,050
By the way, Mr. Xiao.

172
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:31,650
The girl applying for the assistant job is waiting outside.

173
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,060
Forget it, Lao'er.

174
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,120
I've seen so many of them.

175
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,640
None of them were suitable.

176
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,320
You really have to see this one.

177
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,280
That confident?

178
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,080
Alright, bring her in.

179
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,760
Okay.

180
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:02,960
Hello, Manager.
